Orelox (cefodoxime) in typhoid fever. To study the efficacy of Orelox (Cefodoxime) in Typhoid fever in children.Open, non-comparative, multicentre study carried out in GP settings in various cities of Pakistan.Children aged 1-15 years were included in the study. Positive Widal test was the only diagnostic inclusion criteria.Four centers participated in the study. Of the total 77 patients (51 males and 26 females), 61 (79%) cured, 5 (7%) improved (less severe signs and symptoms) and 11 (14%) failures.Treatment of typhoid fever in this study showed 86% efficacy in producing clinical responses suggesting that this drug can be effectively and safely used in the treatment of typhoid fever in children.